---
alwaysApply: true
---
docs:
  updates:
    description: "Whenever a change affects a user-facing feature (symptom library, AI features, highlighting, appointment directory, admin UI, clinical review workflow, role-based access, preferences, onboarding, or navigation), update the relevant documentation pages inside `docs-site/pages/`. The docs are a Nextra site deployed on Vercel at https://docs.signpostingtool.co.uk — there is no longer a Jekyll/GitHub-Pages `/docs` folder or a GitHub Wiki."

    sourceOfTruth:
      - "docs-site/pages/ — the MDX documentation pages (file-based routing)"
      - "docs-site/pages/release-notes.mdx — authoritative source for release information"
      - "docs-site/pages/index.mdx — carries the version banner"
      - "docs-site/CLAUDE.md — conventions for the docs site"

    whenToUpdate:
      - "Feature additions or removals"
      - "Significant UI changes"
      - "Workflow modifications"
      - "Permission changes"
      - "New user-facing capabilities"
      - "Onboarding feature changes or setup workflow modifications"
      - "When pages are added, removed, or renamed"

    maintenanceChecklist:
      description: "When shipping or modifying a user-facing feature, update the affected page(s), the release notes, and the version banner"
      requiredActions:
        - "Update the affected page(s) under docs-site/pages/ to reflect the change"
        - "Add user-visible changes to docs-site/pages/release-notes.mdx (New / Updated / Fixed / For system administrators)"
        - "Bump the version banner on docs-site/pages/index.mdx when the app version changes"
        - "Add or update the relevant _meta.ts entry when a page is added, removed, or renamed"

    conventions:
      - "Sidebar structure and ordering are defined by _meta.ts files in each folder"
      - "Internal links use absolute paths, e.g. /features/symptom-library"
      - "Images go in docs-site/public/images/ and are referenced as /images/filename.png"
      - "Always include cross-links to related pages"
      - "Keep the NHS tone: clear, plain English, no jargon (reading age 9-12)"
      - "Do NOT add manual 'Last updated' lines — the footer timestamp is generated from git at build time"

    documentationLinks:
      description: "Keep in-app documentation links aligned with the public docs site."
      requiredActions:
        - "Update the in-app Docs/Documentation links whenever the documentation URL or access pattern changes."
        - "Refresh the relevant documentation pages to describe any new locations for documentation links."

    whatNotToUpdate:
      - "Do not duplicate release notes content across pages"
      - "Do not include deep code-level details outside the Developer Guide"
      - "Do not update for bug fixes that don't change user-facing behaviour"
